properties.description: A stunning Grade I listed Georgian villa designed by the architect of the Bank of England. Set in more than 200 acres of magnificent parkland overlooking Danson Lake.
properties.name: Danson House

properties.description: Office space that combines the wisdom of well-built industrial spaces with innovative design, sustainable principles, future-proof flexibility and panoramic views. It has achieved BREEAM Outstanding.
properties.name: White Collar Factory

properties.description: An architectural landmark, providing a striking addition to the regeneration and vibrancy of Paddington. Providing high quality flexible office space with great natural light, column-free floors, rooftop terraces and a canalside setting.
properties.name: Brunel Building

properties.description: Yorkton Workshops was restored from a series of dilapidated Victorian stables into a new permanent studio, archive and workshop for Pearson Lloyd. The space also provides a gallery, event space and location available for hire.
properties.name: Yorkton Workshops

properties.description: Guided Tour of the Mosque. Learn about the purpose of a mosque, listen to the call for prayer, observe worshippers offering prayers, ask any questions, get free souvenirs & literature. Refreshments will be served throughout the day
properties.name: Baitul Amn Mosque

properties.description: This mixed-use scheme completed in June 2020 and comprises 322,000sqft offices, 43,000sqft residential (10,000 sq ft affordable housing), 12,000sqft retail and a new pocket park. It has been designed by leading architects Make.
properties.name: 80 Charlotte Street

properties.description: Around 35% of Londoners were born outside the UK - it’s  always been a city of immigrants and refugees. Hear the stories of the bankers, the builders, the child refugees and the rogues and their impact on the City for over 2000 years.
properties.name: Immigrant  London

properties.description: Going back to the 11th century, discover the rich and turbulent history of so many of our queens. Investigate river pageants, the role of the Tower and wine fountains. Shudder at the fate of Lady Jane Grey, queen for only 9 days, and more..
properties.name: Queens, Crowns, Coronations, Executions and more

properties.description: Colindale played a pivotal role in early aviation in England with the establishment of the London Aerodrome. Later, the area was developed with manufacturing, scientific, and cultural repositories and became home to emerging suburbs.
properties.name: Discovering Colindale - How Early Aviation Forged Colindale’s Development

properties.description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
properties.name: Fore Street Art Trail

properties.description: Open House of 13 Nubia Way  and oral history exhibition of Europe's largest black-led community self-build for rent  iintiative including archive material and new video. https://sites.gold.ac.uk/inlivingmemory/tomorrow-is-built-today/
properties.name: 'Tomorrow is Built Today' exhibition of Black-led self-build
